			<p class="show-text">
				People of Luxembourg speak a variety of languages. The national language is Luxembourgish, which is a blend of German, Dutch and French. However, the
government uses French, the newspapers are usually in German, and most people speak English as well!

			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
	
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				
				Luxembourg was established as a Grand Duchy in 963, and today it is the only country in the world ruled by a grand duke. In 1919, Grand Duchess of Charlotte put the royal family up for a public vote to see if the people wanted them in power or wanted them gone. The people voted to keep the grand duchy.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
